This paper deals with the problem of synthesizing high-quality facial photos from sketches and vice versa, which is a well-studied problem in computer vision and graphics. The paper proposes a novel synthesis framework using multi-adversarial networks, which is a recent development in generative models and has shown promising results in image-to-image translation problems. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also discusses the use of various loss functions and iterative synthesis to improve the quality of the generated images, which are topics that are relevant to machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the paper may also belong to the sub-categories cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on two datasets and performs image quality assessment and photo-sketch matching experiments, which are topics that are relevant to computer graphics and visualization. Therefore, the paper may also belong to the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics).
